<center><h2><font color="red">Training Types Information</font></h2></center></br></br>
<font color="Brown" size="5">
The requirement of Training of Running staff is as follows:-</font>
<br><br>
<font color="Brown" size="4">
<u>Loco Running Staff</u>
<br>
<ul>
i)   Technical Training for the type of the Locomotive at a training school<br>
ii) Traffic Training at a training school.<br>
iii) Handling of the locomotive either at Training school or at the division level.<br>
iv) Learning Road of a particular section on which the staff has to run the<br>
    locomotive.
  </ul>
On completion of (i) & (iii) above, competency certificate is issued SrDEE / SrDME to certify
him fit to operate on a particular section and particular loco type
<br><br>

<u>Traffic Running Staff</u>
<br>
<ul>
i) Traffic Training at a training school.<br>
ii) Learning Road of a particular section on which the staff has to run the locomotive<br>
</ul>

Normally in case of disqualification in a promotional training of the running staff he can be
sent maximum upto 3 attempts.
Normally every crew depot should have about 50% of staff competent to officiate in higher
grades so that in case of shortage, staff can be sent to work trains. For sending staff for
promotion courses staff has to be sent depending on their seniority and suitability for
promotion in higher grades.
<br></br>
<u>Initial induction Training</u><br><br>

A Loco running staff has to be trained at school and should have been given handling of that
Locomotive to treat him fit for a particular locomotive. The staff is issued competency
certificate by SrDEE/TrO or SrDME for staff to be considered fit for a particular Loco motives</br>
<br>
Diesel/Electric Assistant Drivers are inducted after initial training including traction (DSL or
Elect), transportation, simulator etc. It normally takes 39 week from the date of induction to
get the qualified Asst Driver.

<br></br>
<u>Promotional Training</u><br></br>
Promotion Training is prescribed for promotion from Asstt Driver to Shunter, Asstt/Shunter to
Goods Driver, and Goods drivers to Passenger Drivers. Promotion training includes Traction
and Transportation Course<br>
<ul>
    C R - Combined Traction and Transportation at BSL.<br>
    W.R - Separate Traction and Transportation promotion courses at BRCY (Electric),</br>
        RTM, SBI & ABR (Diesel) and at UDZ (Transportation).</br>
    N.R. - Separate Traction and Transportation promotion courses, Dsl Traction Training at</br>
    TKD, BGKT, AMV & LDH and transportation at CH.</br>
    - Electric Combined Traction/Transport Training at GMC.
</ul>
Normally every crew depot should have about 50% of staff competent to officiate in higher
grades so that in case of shortage, staff can be sent for promotion courses depending on
their seniority.
